# S07 Angular Setup

# S07 E056 Introduction
    Installing the Angular CLI
    Creating the Angular project
    Setting up VS Code for Angular
    Setting up Angular to use HTTPS
    Adding Angular Material and Tailwind CSS

    Goal:

    To have a working Angular application running on HTTPS

    To understand angular standalone components and how we use them to build an app.

    Major release every 6 months

    1-3 minor releases for each major

    A patch release build almost every week

    At time of recording Angular is on v16

# S07 E057 Creating the Angular app
    angular.dev/references/versions

    installing node with node version manager
    https://joachim8675309.medium.com/installing-node-js-with-nvm-4dc469c977d9

    or

    https://github.com/coreybutler/nvm-windows/releases

    nvm use 22.16.0
    npm install -g @angular/cli

    Set-ExecutionPolicy -Scope CurrentUser -ExecutionPolicy RemoteSigned

    ng new client
    Yes
    No
    Sass SCSS
        cd client
        ng serve
    
